<item>
            <title>[LU-18771] lfs mirror extend mirrored file</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18771</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lfs mirror extend can only merge a non-mirrored layout file, so that when we try to merge multiple mirrors with &quot;-N&quot; option, it needs to call mirror extend multiple times. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18746&quot; title=&quot;&amp;#39;lfs mirror extend&amp;#39; should allow creating a new STALE mirror&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18746&quot;&gt;LU-18746&lt;/a&gt; allows to create stale mirror, we could take a further step to extend mirrored layout, and this implies the to-be-merged mirrors would be marked stale, and they can be resyn-ed later with &quot;lfs mirror resync&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
